TITLE: Creating and Populating a ListVector in Java Arrow
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to build a ListVector of integers using UnionListWriter. The example builds a vector with 10 elements, where each element is a list of 5 values calculated as j*i.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/main/docs/source/java/vector.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
try (BufferAllocator allocator = new RootAllocator(Long.MAX_VALUE);
  ListVector listVector = ListVector.empty("vector", allocator)) {
  UnionListWriter writer = listVector.getWriter();
  for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
     writer.startList();
     writer.setPosition(i);
     for (int j = 0; j < 5; j++) {
         writer.writeInt(j * i);
     }
     writer.setValueCount(5);
     writer.endList();
  }
  listVector.setValueCount(10);
}
```

